---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie policy — oriz"
  description="What cookies oriz uses."
  wordmarkSubtitle="legal"
>
  <header class="spine page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">oriz</a> / <a href="/legal/">legal</a> / cookies</p>
    <h1>Cookie policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </header>

  <article class="spine prose">
    <p>
      oriz uses the smallest set of cookies and storage we can get away with.
    </p>

    <h2>What we set</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Consent notice flag</strong> — a single <code>localStorage</code>
        key remembers you dismissed the privacy notice. No cookie, no tracking.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Site-specific preferences</strong> — individual sites may set
        their own <code>localStorage</code> keys (e.g. journal autosave,
        recently-viewed cards). See each site's own policy for details.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Cloudflare</strong> may set anti-abuse cookies (Turnstile, bot
        management). These are essential for site availability.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Giscus / GitHub</strong> (where comments are enabled) sets
        cookies if you sign in to comment on GitHub.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Google AdSense</strong> (once approved) may set advertising
        cookies. The consent banner lets you opt out per-purpose.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Opting out</h2>
    <p>
      You can clear localStorage and cookies for any oriz domain from your
      browser's site-data settings. Auth will reset to defaults.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
